comment:
Recently, around the same time, I received a call from one of my office colleagues. He said there were openings in their business franchise and asked if I‚Äôd be willing to join. I agreed, and we arranged a meeting. During the meeting, he asked if I could dedicate 4 hours a day and whether I was ambitious about business. I said yes.

Later, they asked me to meet someone else who asked me a few more questions. After the discussion, they said they were okay with me joining their group. However, they said I would need to pay 5.5 lakhs as capital and an additional 1.5 lakhs for a business trip abroad to meet their partners. They fixed a day for me to meet a senior member who would explain everything. They said if I liked what I heard, I could proceed, otherwise it was okay to back out.

They claimed they were earning more than 1 lakh every week, with some buying houses in Dubai, luxury watches, and cars. One person said, ‚ÄúI‚Äôm just 25 and already earning a fancy amount.‚Äù I agreed to hear more. When I asked about the actual business, I realized it was not what they claimed.selling good directly based on requirements is diff but hear they are cheating people by saying you have potential growth buy doing this business 

It seemed like they were deceiving people by calling it a franchise. They asked for a 6.5 lakh investment, suggested taking a loan, and promised high returns. They said I would have to buy products like water purifiers, watches, and other items‚Äîi know this if i buy they would earn 20-30% commission on them.what ever i purchased next on words as well they get commission.

When I questioned why I should buy products I don‚Äôt need, they said, ‚ÄúWithout using the product, how will you do business?‚Äù It became clear that their main goal was to recruit as many people as possible, take their money, and keep the cycle going. They even said if want small amount be a direct seller without joins people but get little amount will get i you want more have to bring in more people to recover my investment for thus they will train you which group of people you need to target how to target and how to let them curious about making-money. 

It‚Äôs obvious now: this is not a real business but a recruitment-based model where only the people at the top make money.
